UNITED STATES of America, Plaintiff-Ap-pellee, v. Angelo ANNUNZIATO, Defendant-Appellant, and Charles F. Gordon, Defendant. No. 448. Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. May 21, 1934. Pinto & Mareantonio, of New York City, for appellant. Martin Conboy, U. S. Atty., of New York City (George R. Pfann, Asst. U. S. Atty., of New York City, of counsel), for the United States.

Before MANTON, SWAN, and CHASE, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Judgment of conviction affirmed.
